// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/sema/emit-ast-resolved/hello.test — post-Sema `-emit=ast`
// golden corpus (T025 of `specs/006-m3-sema/tasks.md`). Asserts:
//
//   - `emit-ast-format.contract.md` Invariant 2: every `Expr` line
//     gains a ` : <Type>` suffix between `loc=` and the kind-
//     specific fields.
//   - `emit-ast-format.contract.md` Invariant 3: every name-ref
//     whose resolved Symbol* is non-null gains a ` -> decl@<file>:<line>:<col>`
//     suffix after the type suffix.
//   - `sema-stability.contract.md` Invariant 1: the printer's
//     output is byte-stable across two runs (per `byte_stable.test`).
//
// **Failing-state evidence (FR-029)**: against the unchanged tree
// at the Phase 2 commit, the post-Sema enrichments are absent
// — the `: <Type>` suffix and `-> decl@…` suffix do not appear in
// the printer output. Phase 3's ResolutionPass + printer extension
// makes them appear; this fixture freezes the format.
//
// RUN: printf 'module hello {\n  reg q[8] = 0;\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: (CompilationUnit
// CHECK:   (ModuleBlock {{.*}}name=hello
// CHECK:     (RegDecl {{.*}}name=q
// CHECK:       (LiteralExpr {{.*}} : BitVector({{[0-9]+}}) kind=Decimal value=8)
// CHECK:       (LiteralExpr {{.*}} : BitVector({{[0-9]+}}) kind=Decimal value=0)
